org.jenkinsci.plugins.IBM_zOS_Connector

Class zFTPConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jenkinsci.plugins.IBM_zOS_Connector.zFTPConnector

  • public class zFTPConnector
extends java.lang.Object

    zFTPConnector

    FTP-based communication with z/OS-like systems. Used for submitting jobs, fetching job log and extraction of MaxCC.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Alexander Shcherbakov

      • submit

        public boolean submit(java.io.InputStream inputStream,
             boolean wait,
             int waitTime,
             java.io.OutputStream outputStream,
             boolean deleteLogFromSpool)
        Submit job for execution.
        Parameters:
        inputStream - JCL text of the job.
        wait - Whether we need for the job to complete.
        waitTime - Maximum wait time in minutes. If set to 0, will wait forever.
        outputStream - Stream to put job log. Can be Null.
        deleteLogFromSpool - Whether the job log should be deleted fro spool upon job end.
        Returns:
        Whether the job was successfully submitted and the job log was fetched.
        jobCC holds the response of the operation (including errors).
        See Also:
        connect(), logon(), waitForCompletion(OutputStream), deleteJobLog()
